    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_529996">Ya know what would make me buy ebooks?  Give me an electronic version when I buy the real book.  I LOVE real books - but I love my Kindle for ease of use.  It's much easier to carry my Kindle around and have dozens/hundreds of books than to try and carry even 2 books around (ie, I finish one while I'm out and now I have nothing left to read)...<br />
<br />
I have thousands of real books.  I have 35000 ebooks - most of which I will never read.  But I have to &quot;find&quot; copies of books I legitimately own.  Give me an ebook copy when I buy a real copy and I would likely never &quot;find&quot; another book.  I love my collection of books, I'm trying to build bookshelves to hold all my books, but...  again, convenience outweighs my love of real books.  If I buy a copy on Amazon and can instantly have a copy, then get a copy for my bookshelf in a few days...  I'd be in heaven.  But I'm not buying a book twice.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
