    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_530001">The problem with this is eBooks are not the same product as a printed book, so it's unreasonable to expect it for free.  This would be like taking all your VHS movies back to the store and expecting them to give you DVDs for free.<br />
<br />
As someone who works in the eBook industry, I'm excited but cautious of this news.  It's cool that those three companies won't be price fixing anymore (which was really shady to begin with) but no one I have talked to knows just how publishers are going to go about reimbursing customers.</div>
