    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_530002">This has me pretty excited, too. I've pretty much given up maintaining a general library. I move too often and eBooks let me keep a large library without the clutter. A pulpy steampunk novel or a harry potter book is not a collector's item, imo, and doesn't really merit a physical copy. OTOH, if I find good condition but old prints of something related to what I want my library/collection to revolve around, I still will immediately pick that up. Seems that in this day and age, unless you're creating a collection, there really isn't much to physical books over their electronic counterpart--hell, you can even annotate eBooks pretty easily now.</div>
