</div>No one is against authors being paid - we're not saying you can't charge for an ebook version...  we're saying if we buy the paper copy, we should get a digital copy included (either free, or with a small fee).  I like printed books, but I like the convenience of my e-reader as well.  I shouldn't have to buy a paper book, and a digital book, to meet my needs.  I buy lots of books, then have to go &quot;find&quot; an electronic copy.  If it cost an extra buck, I'd just pay it when I bought the book.</div>
